      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CINNAMON (7) only beat a couple home when well fancied over a longer trip at her latest appearance but had kicked off the campaign with a second at this circuit and distance prior. Race fit third-up and should enjoy a nice smother from this draw. Leading hope if she gets the gaps. TRY CATCHING ME (4) has the hoof on the till after seconds in her three starts at this venue since a spell. Produced another strong performance last time when she came from the back row to miss narrowly. Should be at her peak now so can break through. BULL SHARK (2) didn't do a bad job when 6m away last time out and placed at Newcastle prior. Draws for a good showing. ESPERANZA (9) is worth some thought after coming from this barrier to be beaten only 4.6m here last week.",
